cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about incorporating source syntax into neural machine translation (NMT), which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes different types of encoders to incorporate source syntax into NMT, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also evaluates the proposed models on Chinese-to-English translation, which involves text and language processing, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper may also involve computer vision techniques for analyzing the results, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
